<subSubSection id="E9C665140768FFF31013067FFA28AAE8" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" type="description">
<paragraph id="A163369F0768FFF31013067FFC5AABA8" blockId="16.[811,1458,1141,1390]" box="[813,962,1141,1167]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F0768FFF31013069EFB9CAB8B" blockId="16.[811,1458,1141,1390]" box="[813,1028,1172,1198]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF31013069EFB9CAB8B" box="[813,1028,1172,1198]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Thoracic appendages</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F0768FFF3101306BEFA37AA4B" blockId="16.[811,1458,1141,1390]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Chelate P1; elongated P1 propodus, subrectangular, dorsoventrally compressed, with a longitudinal bulge on ventral surface; narrow dactylar bulge, slightly bulged, not posteriorly delimited by a groove; slender, elongated fingers, almost straight; occlusal margins with wide conical teeth, regularly spaced; P1 carpus short, subtriangular; elongated P1 merus.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F0768FFF310130799FC4CAA88" blockId="16.[813,980,1427,1453]" box="[813,980,1427,1453]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">
