<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF310130799FC4CAA88" box="[813,980,1427,1453]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Ornamentation</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A163369F0768FFF3101307B9FA28AAE8" blockId="16.[813,1456,1459,1485]" box="[813,1456,1459,1485]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">P1 propodus and fingers densely covered by fine tubercles.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9C665140768FFF3101307F9FA32A8CE" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A163369F0768FFF3101307F9FA32A8CE" blockId="16.[810,1457,1523,2027]" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">
DISCUSSION This species is only known by some isolated P1, mainly from the lithographic limestones of southern 
<collectingCountry id="D9CB760F0768FFF316290439FAE7A968" box="[1303,1407,1587,1613]" name="Germany" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Germany</collectingCountry>
. The subrectangular, dorso-ventrally compressed propodus with long and narrowing fingers justifies the assignation to 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3165C0479FA3EA9A9" authorityName="Meyer" authorityYear="1840" box="[1378,1446,1651,1676]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3165C0479FA3EA9A9" box="[1378,1446,1651,1676]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Eryma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3107D0499FC55A989" authorityName="Oppel" authorityYear="1861" box="[835,973,1683,1708]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3107D0499FC55A989" box="[835,973,1683,1708]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">Eryma major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is only known by some fragments of P1, so the comparisons are restricted to the species for which the P1 are also known (
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF310DD04D9FBD7A9C9" box="[995,1103,1747,1772]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="georgeii">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF310DD04D9FBD7A9C9" box="[995,1103,1747,1772]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. georgeii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3176104D9FB7CA9C9" authorityName="Feldmann &amp; Titus" authorityYear="2006" box="[1119,1252,1747,1772]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jungostrix">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3176104D9FB7CA9C9" box="[1119,1252,1747,1772]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. jungostrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF317CA04D9FAD0A9C9" baseAuthorityName="Etallon" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[1268,1352,1746,1772]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lerasi">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF317CA04D9FAD0A9C9" box="[1268,1352,1746,1772]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. lerasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3166604D9FCE2A829" baseAuthorityName="Meyer" baseAuthorityYear="1840" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandelslohi">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3166604D9FCE2A829" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. mandelslohi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF310B904F9FBB5A829" baseAuthorityName="Schlotheim" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[903,1069,1778,1804]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modestiforme">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF310B904F9FBB5A829" box="[903,1069,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. modestiforme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3170504F9FA8EA829" authorityName="Trautschold" authorityYear="1866" box="[1083,1302,1778,1804]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadriverrucatum">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3170504F9FA8EA829" box="[1083,1302,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. quadriverrucatum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3161D04F9FA30A829" baseAuthorityName="Munster" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1315,1448,1778,1804]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="veltheimii">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3161D04F9FA30A829" box="[1315,1448,1778,1804]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. veltheimii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF310130518FC28A80E" authorityName="Erymoidea" baseAuthorityName="Meyer" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[813,944,1810,1835]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventrosum">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF310130518FC28A80E" box="[813,944,1810,1835]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. ventrosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF310820518FBAEA809" authorityName="Schweigert, Dietl &amp; Roper" authorityYear="2000" box="[956,1078,1810,1836]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="westphali">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF310820518FBAEA809" box="[956,1078,1810,1836]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. westphali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The straight fingers of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3160F0518FA11A80E" authorityName="Oppel" authorityYear="1861" box="[1329,1417,1810,1835]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3160F0518FA11A80E" box="[1329,1417,1810,1835]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are clearly distinct from the curved ones of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF317E50538FADFA86E" box="[1243,1351,1842,1867]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="georgeii">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF317E50538FADFA86E" box="[1243,1351,1842,1867]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. georgeii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3166B0538FA30A86E" baseAuthorityName="Etallon" baseAuthorityYear="1861" box="[1365,1448,1841,1867]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lerasi">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3166B0538FA30A86E" box="[1365,1448,1841,1867]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. lerasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF310130558FC25A84E" baseAuthorityName="Meyer" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[813,957,1873,1899]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mandelslohi">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF310130558FC25A84E" box="[813,957,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. mandelslohi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF310F60558FBDDA84E" baseAuthorityName="Munster" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[968,1093,1873,1899]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="veltheimii">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF310F60558FBDDA84E" box="[968,1093,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. veltheimii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3176E0558FB57A84E" authorityName="Erymoidea" baseAuthorityName="Meyer" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[1104,1231,1874,1899]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ventrosum">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3176E0558FB57A84E" box="[1104,1231,1874,1899]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E.ventrosum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3163A0558FAE2A84E" authorityName="Schweigert, Dietl &amp; Roper" authorityYear="2000" box="[1284,1402,1873,1899]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="westphali">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3163A0558FAE2A84E" box="[1284,1402,1873,1899]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E.westphali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The propodus of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3108D0578FB94A8AE" authorityName="Oppel" authorityYear="1861" box="[947,1036,1906,1931]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3108D0578FB94A8AE" box="[947,1036,1906,1931]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is also shorter than that of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF316140578FA36A8AE" baseAuthorityName="Munster" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1322,1454,1905,1931]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="veltheimii">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF316140578FA36A8AE" box="[1322,1454,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. veltheimii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF310610598FC79A88E" authorityName="Schweigert, Dietl &amp; Roper" authorityYear="2000" box="[863,993,1937,1963]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="westphali">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF310610598FC79A88E" box="[863,993,1937,1963]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. westphali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The propodus of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF317860598FA8EA88E" authorityName="Oppel" authorityYear="1861" box="[1208,1302,1938,1963]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="major">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF317860598FA8EA88E" box="[1208,1302,1938,1963]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. major</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is covered by tubercles while that of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3172805B8FB0FA8EE" baseAuthorityName="Munster" baseAuthorityYear="1839" box="[1046,1175,1969,1995]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="veltheimii">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3172805B8FB0FA8EE" box="[1046,1175,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. veltheimii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF317F705B8FADBA8EE" authorityName="Schweigert, Dietl &amp; Roper" authorityYear="2000" box="[1225,1347,1969,1995]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="westphali">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF317F705B8FADBA8EE" box="[1225,1347,1969,1995]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. westphali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is smooth and that of 
<taxonomicName id="66DC4D1C0768FFF3109505D8FBC8A8CE" baseAuthorityName="Schlotheim" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[939,1104,2001,2027]" class="Malacostraca" family="Erymidae" genus="Eryma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="16" pageNumber="39" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="modestiforme">
<emphasis id="93A8EA8D0768FFF3109505D8FBC8A8CE" box="[939,1104,2001,2027]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="39">E. modestiforme</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is covered by small depressions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
